```python
# Functions for initializing a silicon object
def SIMS_read(csv_in, num_shots=1):
    """Read and normalize in SIMS data."""
    maski = csv_in["C i"] != ""
    depth_list_i = np.array(csv_in["Depth (µm) i"][maski].astype(float))
    density_list_i = np.array(csv_in["C i"][maski].astype(float))
    density_one_shot_i = density_list_i / num_shots

    maskii = csv_in["C ii"] != ""
    depth_list_ii = np.array(csv_in["Depth (µm) ii"][maskii].astype(float))
    density_list_ii = np.array(csv_in["C ii"][maskii].astype(float))
    density_one_shot_ii = density_list_ii / num_shots

    maskiii = csv_in["C iii"] != ""
    depth_list_iii = np.array(csv_in["Depth (µm) iii"][maskiii].astype(float))
    density_list_iii = np.array(csv_in["C iii"][maskiii].astype(float))
    density_one_shot_iii = density_list_iii / num_shots
    return np.array(
        (
            [depth_list_i, density_one_shot_i],
            [depth_list_ii, density_one_shot_ii],
            [depth_list_iii, density_one_shot_iii],
        ), dtype="object"
    )


def read_srim(srim_file):
    srim_res = np.loadtxt(
        srim_file,
        dtype=str,
        skiprows=23,
        max_rows=88,
    )

    # Ion energy is in kev and MeV; convert all to MeV
    ion_energy = srim_res[:, 0].astype(float)
    mask_wrong_energy_unit = srim_res[:, 1] == "keV"
    ion_energy[mask_wrong_energy_unit] /= 1e3

    # Ion projected range is in A, mm, and um; convert all to um
    proj_range = srim_res[:, 4].astype(float)
    mask_wrong_unit_A = srim_res[:, 5] == "A"
    mask_wrong_unit_mm = srim_res[:, 5] == "mm"
    proj_range[mask_wrong_unit_A] /= 1e4
    proj_range[mask_wrong_unit_mm] *= 1e3

    srim_df = pd.DataFrame({"Energy": ion_energy, "Projected Range (um)": proj_range})

    return srim_df


def depths_to_energies_srim(sims_depth):
    srim_df = read_srim(C_SRIM_file)
    energies_arr = np.interp(
        sims_depth,
        srim_df["Projected Range (um)"],
        srim_df["Energy"],
    )

    return energies_arr


def energies_to_depth_srim(sims_energy):
    srim_df = read_srim(C_SRIM_file)
    energies_arr = np.interp(
        sims_energy,
        srim_df["Energy"],
        srim_df["Projected Range (um)"],
    )

    return energies_arr


def exponential(x, a, b, c):
    return a * b ** (c * x)

def gaussian(x, mu, sig):
    return np.exp(-np.power(x - mu, 2.) / (2 * np.power(sig, 2.)))
```

```python
# Functions for evolving a silicon object
def find_stepsize(array):
    stepsizes = np.around((array[1:] - array[:-1]), decimals=12)
    stepsize = stepsizes[0]
    if np.all(stepsizes == stepsize):
        return stepsize
    else:
        print("Array has a non-uniform stepsize.")


def round_sig(x, sig=2):
    if x != 0.0:
        return round(x, sig - int(np.floor(np.log10(np.abs(x)))) - 1)
    else:
        return x
    
def round_up(value):
    return np.ceil(value / 100.0) * 100
```

```python
# Functions for calculating F0 in the evolution of silicon temperature grid
def calc_alpha_solid(temp_val):
    # (kg/m3)
    rho = (2.33 - 2.19e-5 * temp_val) * 1000
    # (W/m*K)
    k = 100 * (
        -5.06658e-16 * temp_val ** 5
        + 3.10542e-12 * temp_val ** 4
        - 7.51910e-9 * temp_val ** 3
        + 9.07707e-6 * temp_val ** 2
        - 5.63226e-03 * temp_val
        + 2.11025
    )
    # (J/kg*K)
    Cp = (23.5 + 3.05e-3 * temp_val - 2.93e-7 * temp_val ** 2) / 28.0855 * 1000
    alpha = k / (rho * Cp)

    return alpha


def calc_alpha_liquid(temp_val):
    # (kg/m3)
    rho = (2.54 - 2.19e-5 * temp_val - 1.21e-8 * temp_val ** 2) * 1000
    # (W/m*K)
    k = 100 * 0.82
    # (J/kg*K)
    Cp = 29 / 28.0855 * 1000
    alpha = k / (rho * Cp)

    return alpha


def calc_alpha_gas(temp_val):
    # (kg/m3)
    rho = 2311.0567276
    # (W/m*K)
    k = 100 * 0.82
    # (J/kg*K)
    Cp = 29 / 28.0855 * 1000
    alpha = k / (rho * Cp)

    return alpha


def calc_F0(alpha, dt, dz):
    F0 = alpha * dt / dz ** 2
    return F0
```

```python
class silicon_object:
    def __init__(
        self,
        n_shots: int,
        min_idx: int,
    ):
        """Create an object that stores a list containing a grid of temperatures at time t=0."""
        temp_grid_0 = np.array([])

        # Use data from B06 spot with the highest concentration of atm/cc
        depth = B06_data[2][0]
        atm_per_cm3 = B06_data[2][1]

        # Convert SIMS depth to energies (MeV) using SRIM
        energies = depths_to_energies_srim(depth)

        # Convert SIMS atm/cm^3 into J/cm^3
        J_per_cm3 = J_per_MeV * (atm_per_cm3 * energies)

        # Fitting procedure
        energies_used = energies[min_idx:]
        J_per_cm3_used = J_per_cm3[min_idx:]
        p0 = (10e16, 2, 10)
        params, cv = curve_fit(exponential, energies_used, J_per_cm3_used, p0)
        a, b, c = params

        # Results from fitting
        # Extrapolate out to 600 MeV (which should overshoot the approximate corresponding full depth of the sample – 500 um)
        # 1 um ~= 1 MeV (see SRIM tables)
        energies_extrap = np.linspace(0, 600, 501)
        J_per_cm3_extrap = exponential(energies_extrap, a, b, c)

        # Convert to depth and temperature
        depths_extrap = 1e-6 * energies_to_depth_srim(energies_extrap)
        deltaT_extrap = J_per_cm3_extrap / Cp_rho
        # Make sure all temperatures are at least at room temperature
        deltaT_extrap[deltaT_extrap < 293.0] = 293.0

        # Create new depth array (with uniform step size) and interpolate temperatures
        self.depth = 1e-6 * np.linspace(0, 500, 51)
        deltaT_0 = np.interp(self.depth, depths_extrap, deltaT_extrap)

        # Create a gaussian distribution at each depth with the SIMS concentration being the peak value
        full_width = 50 * 1e-3
        self.width = np.linspace(0, full_width, 51)
        aperture_idx = np.logical_not(
            (self.width >= round(full_width / 2 - 5e-3, 4)) & (self.width <= round(full_width / 2 + 5e-3,4))
        )

        for peak_temp in deltaT_0:
            # Form gaussian distribution and scale by peak temp
            temp_grid_row = peak_temp * gaussian(self.width, full_width / 2, 1e-3 * 15)
            # Zero all points outside of the aperture
            temp_grid_row[aperture_idx] = 0.0
            # Offset all points up to room temperature
            temp_grid_row += 293

            # Add the array of temperatures at each width to an array of temperatures
            if temp_grid_0.size == 0:
                temp_grid_0 = temp_grid_row
            else:
                temp_grid_0 = np.vstack((temp_grid_0, temp_grid_row))

        # Create a list of temperature grids that will house the evolution of the temperature grid over time
        self.temp_grids = [temp_grid_0]

    def evolve_temp_grid(self, temp_arr, dx, dy):
        """Evolve a temperature grid one time step."""
        # Calculate an array alphas to calculate Fourier Numbers
        alpha = np.piecewise(
            temp_arr,
            [temp_arr < 1687, (temp_arr >= 1687) & (temp_arr < 3538), temp_arr >= 3538],
            [
                lambda temp_val: calc_alpha_solid(temp_val),
                lambda temp_val: calc_alpha_liquid(temp_val),
                lambda temp_val: calc_alpha_gas(temp_val),
            ],
        )

        # Set stepsize such that the stability criterion is satisfied
        dt = 0.9 * np.min(
            (dx ** (-2) + dy ** (-2)) ** (-1) * (2 * alpha[alpha >= 0.0]) ** -1
        )
        f0x_arr = calc_F0(alpha, dt, dx)
        f0y_arr = calc_F0(alpha, dt, dy)

        # Evolve all nodes in temperature grid
        # Sum temperatures of surrounding nodes and scale by fourier number(s)
        new_temp_arr = f0x_arr * (
            np.hstack((temp_arr[:, 1:], np.zeros(temp_arr.shape[0])[:, None]))
            + np.hstack((np.zeros(temp_arr.shape[0])[:, None], temp_arr[:, 0:-1]))
        ) + f0y_arr * (
            np.vstack((temp_arr[1:], np.zeros(temp_arr.shape[1])))
            + np.vstack((np.zeros(temp_arr.shape[1]), temp_arr[:-1]))
        )

        # Deal with special case of the edge nodes
        # Top edge
        new_temp_arr[0, :-1][1:] += f0y_arr[0, :-1][1:] * temp_arr[1:2][0][1:-1]
        # Bottom edge
        new_temp_arr[-1, :0:-1][1:] += f0y_arr[-1, :0:-1][1:] * temp_arr[-2:-1][0][1:-1]
        # Left edge
        new_temp_arr[:-1, 0][1:] += f0x_arr[:-1, 0][1:] * temp_arr[:, 1][1:-1]
        # Right edge
        new_temp_arr[:-1, -1][1:] += f0x_arr[:-1, -1][1:] * temp_arr[:, -2][1:-1]

        # Corners
        new_temp_arr[0][0] *= 2
        new_temp_arr[-1][0] *= 2
        new_temp_arr[0][-1] *= 2
        new_temp_arr[-1][-1] *= 2

        new_temp_arr += (1 - 2 * f0x_arr - 2 * f0y_arr) * temp_arr

        return new_temp_arr, dt

    def simulate_sample(self, t_stop, cont=False):
        """Evolve the sample's temperatures over time."""
        x_stepsize = find_stepsize(self.width)
        y_stepsize = find_stepsize(self.depth)

        current_temp_grid = self.temp_grids[-1]
        # Don't reset simulation parameters if continuing simulation
        if cont == False:
            self.time_arr = [0.0]
            iteration = 0
        while self.time_arr[-1] <= t_stop:
            current_temp_grid, t_stepsize = self.evolve_temp_grid(
                current_temp_grid, x_stepsize, y_stepsize
            )
            iteration += 1

            self.temp_grids.append(current_temp_grid)
            self.time_arr.append(self.time_arr[-1] + t_stepsize)
            if iteration % 1e4 == 0:
                print(self.time_arr[-1])
                print()

    def animate_simulation(
        self,
        downsample_factor: int,
        xlim: tuple[float, float] = (None, None),
        ylim: tuple[float, float] = (None, None),
        max_level: float = 1e4,
        scale_down: int = 10,
    ):
        fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
        div = make_axes_locatable(ax1)
        cax = div.append_axes("right", "5%", "5%")

        self.max_level = max_level
        self.levels = np.linspace(293., self.max_level, 51)

        grid_plot = ax1.contourf(
            self.width * 1e3,
            self.depth * 1e6,
            self.temp_grids[0],
            levels=self.levels,
            cmap="plasma",
        )
        cbar = fig.colorbar(grid_plot, cax=cax)
        cbar.set_label(label="Temperature (K)", size=15, rotation=270, labelpad=17.5)

        ax1.set_xlim(xlim)
        ax1.set_ylim(ylim)
        ax1.set_ylabel("Depth (µm)", fontsize=15)
        ax1.set_xlabel("Width (mm)", fontsize=15)
        n_secs_txt = ax1.set_title("0 (s)", fontsize=13)

        def animate(i):
            if (
                np.max(self.temp_grids[int(i ** downsample_factor)])
                < self.max_level / scale_down
            ):
                self.max_level /= scale_down
                self.levels = np.linspace(293., self.max_level, 51)

            grid_plot = ax1.contourf(
                self.width * 1e3,
                self.depth * 1e6,
                self.temp_grids[int(i ** downsample_factor)],
                levels=self.levels,
                cmap="plasma",
            )
            n_secs_txt.set_text(
                f"{round_sig(self.time_arr[int(i ** downsample_factor)])} (s)".format()
            )

            ticks = round_up(np.linspace(300., self.max_level, 8))
            cax.cla()
            cbar = fig.colorbar(grid_plot, cax=cax, ticks=ticks)
            cbar.set_label(
                label="Temperature (K)", size=15, rotation=270, labelpad=17.5
            )
            plt.close()

        n_timesteps = (
            (
                np.linspace(0, len(self.temp_grids), len(self.temp_grids) + 1)
                ** downsample_factor
            )
            < len(self.temp_grids)
        ).sum()
        print(n_timesteps)
        anim = animation.FuncAnimation(fig, animate, frames=n_timesteps)

        plt.close()
        return anim
```

  /* Define the Animation class */
  function Animation(frames, img_id, slider_id, interval, loop_select_id){
    this.img_id = img_id;
    this.slider_id = slider_id;
    this.loop_select_id = loop_select_id;
    this.interval = interval;
    this.current_frame = 0;
    this.direction = 0;
    this.timer = null;
    this.frames = new Array(frames.length);

    for (var i=0; i<frames.length; i++)
    {
     this.frames[i] = new Image();
     this.frames[i].src = frames[i];
    }
    var slider = document.getElementById(this.slider_id);
    slider.max = this.frames.length - 1;
    if (isInternetExplorer()) {
        // switch from oninput to onchange because IE <= 11 does not conform
        // with W3C specification. It ignores oninput and onchange behaves
        // like oninput. In contrast, Microsoft Edge behaves correctly.
        slider.setAttribute('onchange', slider.getAttribute('oninput'));
        slider.setAttribute('oninput', null);
    }
    this.set_frame(this.current_frame);
  }

  Animation.prototype.get_loop_state = function(){
    var button_group = document[this.loop_select_id].state;
    for (var i = 0; i < button_group.length; i++) {
        var button = button_group[i];
        if (button.checked) {
            return button.value;
        }
    }
    return undefined;
  }

  Animation.prototype.set_frame = function(frame){
    this.current_frame = frame;
    document.getElementById(this.img_id).src =
            this.frames[this.current_frame].src;
    document.getElementById(this.slider_id).value = this.current_frame;
  }

  Animation.prototype.next_frame = function()
  {
    this.set_frame(Math.min(this.frames.length - 1, this.current_frame + 1));
  }

  Animation.prototype.previous_frame = function()
  {
    this.set_frame(Math.max(0, this.current_frame - 1));
  }

  Animation.prototype.first_frame = function()
  {
    this.set_frame(0);
  }

  Animation.prototype.last_frame = function()
  {
    this.set_frame(this.frames.length - 1);
  }

  Animation.prototype.slower = function()
  {
    this.interval /= 0.7;
    if(this.direction > 0){this.play_animation();}
    else if(this.direction < 0){this.reverse_animation();}
  }

  Animation.prototype.faster = function()
  {
    this.interval *= 0.7;
    if(this.direction > 0){this.play_animation();}
    else if(this.direction < 0){this.reverse_animation();}
  }

  Animation.prototype.anim_step_forward = function()
  {
    this.current_frame += 1;
    if(this.current_frame < this.frames.length){
      this.set_frame(this.current_frame);
    }else{
      var loop_state = this.get_loop_state();
      if(loop_state == "loop"){
        this.first_frame();
      }else if(loop_state == "reflect"){
        this.last_frame();
        this.reverse_animation();
      }else{
        this.pause_animation();
        this.last_frame();
      }
    }
  }

  Animation.prototype.anim_step_reverse = function()
  {
    this.current_frame -= 1;
    if(this.current_frame >= 0){
      this.set_frame(this.current_frame);
    }else{
      var loop_state = this.get_loop_state();
      if(loop_state == "loop"){
        this.last_frame();
      }else if(loop_state == "reflect"){
        this.first_frame();
        this.play_animation();
      }else{
        this.pause_animation();
        this.first_frame();
      }
    }
  }

  Animation.prototype.pause_animation = function()
  {
    this.direction = 0;
    if (this.timer){
      clearInterval(this.timer);
      this.timer = null;
    }
  }

  Animation.prototype.play_animation = function()
  {
    this.pause_animation();
    this.direction = 1;
    var t = this;
    if (!this.timer) this.timer = setInterval(function() {
        t.anim_step_forward();
    }, this.interval);
  }

  Animation.prototype.reverse_animation = function()
  {
    this.pause_animation();
    this.direction = -1;
    var t = this;
    if (!this.timer) this.timer = setInterval(function() {
        t.anim_step_reverse();
    }, this.interval);
  }
</script>

<script language="javascript">
  function isInternetExplorer() {
    ua = navigator.userAgent;
    /* MSIE used to detect old browsers and Trident used to newer ones*/
    return ua.indexOf("MSIE ") > -1 || ua.indexOf("Trident/") > -1;
  }

  /* Define the Animation class */
  function Animation(frames, img_id, slider_id, interval, loop_select_id){
    this.img_id = img_id;
    this.slider_id = slider_id;
    this.loop_select_id = loop_select_id;
    this.interval = interval;
    this.current_frame = 0;
    this.direction = 0;
    this.timer = null;
    this.frames = new Array(frames.length);

    for (var i=0; i<frames.length; i++)
    {
     this.frames[i] = new Image();
     this.frames[i].src = frames[i];
    }
    var slider = document.getElementById(this.slider_id);
    slider.max = this.frames.length - 1;
    if (isInternetExplorer()) {
        // switch from oninput to onchange because IE <= 11 does not conform
        // with W3C specification. It ignores oninput and onchange behaves
        // like oninput. In contrast, Microsoft Edge behaves correctly.
        slider.setAttribute('onchange', slider.getAttribute('oninput'));
        slider.setAttribute('oninput', null);
    }
    this.set_frame(this.current_frame);
  }

  Animation.prototype.get_loop_state = function(){
    var button_group = document[this.loop_select_id].state;
    for (var i = 0; i < button_group.length; i++) {
        var button = button_group[i];
        if (button.checked) {
            return button.value;
        }
    }
    return undefined;
  }

  Animation.prototype.set_frame = function(frame){
    this.current_frame = frame;
    document.getElementById(this.img_id).src =
            this.frames[this.current_frame].src;
    document.getElementById(this.slider_id).value = this.current_frame;
  }

  Animation.prototype.next_frame = function()
  {
    this.set_frame(Math.min(this.frames.length - 1, this.current_frame + 1));
  }

  Animation.prototype.previous_frame = function()
  {
    this.set_frame(Math.max(0, this.current_frame - 1));
  }

  Animation.prototype.first_frame = function()
  {
    this.set_frame(0);
  }

  Animation.prototype.last_frame = function()
  {
    this.set_frame(this.frames.length - 1);
  }

  Animation.prototype.slower = function()
  {
    this.interval /= 0.7;
    if(this.direction > 0){this.play_animation();}
    else if(this.direction < 0){this.reverse_animation();}
  }

  Animation.prototype.faster = function()
  {
    this.interval *= 0.7;
    if(this.direction > 0){this.play_animation();}
    else if(this.direction < 0){this.reverse_animation();}
  }

  Animation.prototype.anim_step_forward = function()
  {
    this.current_frame += 1;
    if(this.current_frame < this.frames.length){
      this.set_frame(this.current_frame);
    }else{
      var loop_state = this.get_loop_state();
      if(loop_state == "loop"){
        this.first_frame();
      }else if(loop_state == "reflect"){
        this.last_frame();
        this.reverse_animation();
      }else{
        this.pause_animation();
        this.last_frame();
      }
    }
  }

  Animation.prototype.anim_step_reverse = function()
  {
    this.current_frame -= 1;
    if(this.current_frame >= 0){
      this.set_frame(this.current_frame);
    }else{
      var loop_state = this.get_loop_state();
      if(loop_state == "loop"){
        this.last_frame();
      }else if(loop_state == "reflect"){
        this.first_frame();
        this.play_animation();
      }else{
        this.pause_animation();
        this.first_frame();
      }
    }
  }

  Animation.prototype.pause_animation = function()
  {
    this.direction = 0;
    if (this.timer){
      clearInterval(this.timer);
      this.timer = null;
    }
  }

  Animation.prototype.play_animation = function()
  {
    this.pause_animation();
    this.direction = 1;
    var t = this;
    if (!this.timer) this.timer = setInterval(function() {
        t.anim_step_forward();
    }, this.interval);
  }

  Animation.prototype.reverse_animation = function()
  {
    this.pause_animation();
    this.direction = -1;
    var t = this;
    if (!this.timer) this.timer = setInterval(function() {
        t.anim_step_reverse();
    }, this.interval);
  }
</script>
